OL,6,FThe TUC said it believes this "could
OL,7,Fbe the tip of the iceberg" and has
OL,8,Fcalled on the Government to crack down
OL,9,Fon minimum wage breaches as part of
OL,10,Fits reforms to worker rights.
OL,12,FIn April this year, the legal minimum
OL,13,Fwage for workers aged 21 and over
OL,14,Fincreased by 9.8% to #11.44 per hour.
OL,16,FThis would equate to a minimum annual
OL,17,Fsalary of #20,820.20 for a full-time
OL,18,Frole of 35 hours per week.
